hopobject.body: Very Good Site cahealthie.inslinevb.com "Robotic" isn't the right word for Sturgeon; "enamelled" might be better, or perhaps just "neat and careful". She points out the danger of generalisations even as she makes them. When I asked her what social class her parents belonged to, she noted that there was "always a bit of subjectivity about these things" before describing them as working-class. In fact, her father was an engineer for Chubb locks. She was born in Ayrshire in 1970 and grew up near Irvine with parents who rarely discussed politics, and who were politicised by their daughter (her mother is now an SNP councillor and provost of North Ayrshire) rather than the other way around.
